The assay buffer used for proteolytic assays was Tris buffered saline (20 mM Tris, 150 mM NaCl, 5 mM CaCl2, 0.1% Bovine serum albumin (BSA), 5% dimethly sulfoxide (DMSO) pH 7.4). In a 96-well microtiter plate, inhibitor was serially diluted to give a range of final concentrations from 0.01 nM to 10 μM. Duplicate sets of wells were assayed and control wells without inhibitor were included.
